{
	"name": "Ginkgo Biloba",
	"type": "object",
	"img": "icons/consumables/plants/leaf-elm-glowing-green.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Ginkgo trees are tall, with leaves growing either from the tips of branches or from embedded buds near the base of the trunk. The fan-shaped leaves have two or more lobes and a rich green color with prominent veins. In the fall, the leaves turn a brilliant yellow or gold. Ginkgo can help improve memory in people with dementia.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Effect.</strong></em> For 1 hour after being ingested, a dose of ginkgo biloba enables a creature to repeat a failed saving throw against the [[/condition id=confused]] condition, and it grants an expertise die on Engineering, History, or Religion checks to recall information. A companion can administer a dose of ginkgo following all the rules for administering a potion. Note that if a second dose is ingested in the same 24-hour period, you must also make a successful DC 13 Constitution saving throw or be [[/condition id=poisoned]] for 24 hours.</p>",
